00:02:57,377 --> 00:02:59,379
WHO WANTS TO JUMP ON BOARD

00:02:59,379 --> 00:03:03,016
THIS TOTALLY TUBULAR OPPORTUNITY
WITH US?

00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:04,251
HOW DID YOU
COME UP WITH THIS?

00:03:04,251 --> 00:03:08,021
Rachel: A FARMER 30 YEARS AGO
MADE ONE FOR HIS GRANDKIDS,

00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:11,391
AND HE SOLD A FEW TO, YOU KNOW,
PRESCHOOLS AND LOCAL PLACES.

00:03:11,391 --> 00:03:13,193
SO MY PARENTS
ACTUALLY BOUGHT ONE.

00:03:13,193 --> 00:03:15,262
I GREW UP
JUMPING ON THE ORIGINAL.

00:03:15,262 --> 00:03:17,297
THEN YEARS PASSED BY.

00:03:17,297 --> 00:03:20,167
ALL OF US KIDS WANTED ONE
NOW THAT WE HAVE FAMILIES.

00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:22,436
WE CONTACTED THE FARMER,
AND, SADLY, HE HAD PASSED AWAY.

00:03:22,436 --> 00:03:26,006
WE ENDED UP MANUFACTURING IT
FROM THAT POINT FORWARD.

00:03:26,006 --> 00:03:27,207
AND YOU OWN
THE RIGHTS TO IT?

00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,208
YES.
WE OWN THE FULL RIGHTS.

00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,242
SO YOU HAVE A PATENT

00:03:29,242 --> 00:03:30,444
ON THE BOUNCY, ROUND THING?

00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:32,279
WE HAVE A PROVISIONAL
THAT'S FILED.

00:03:32,279 --> 00:03:34,981
WE HAVE A UTILITY AND DESIGN
THAT ARE ALSO PENDING.

00:03:34,981 --> 00:03:37,084
AND HOW MUCH OF YOUR OWN MONEY'S
IN THIS?

00:03:37,084 --> 00:03:39,352
Rachel:
WE HAVE PUT $144,000 CASH --

00:03:39,352 --> 00:03:41,154
WE HAVE NO DEBT...
WOW.

00:03:41,154 --> 00:03:42,222
GOOD FOR YOU.
...OF OUR OWN
PERSONAL MONEY.

00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,390
GOOD FOR YOU.

00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:45,292
BUT WE HAVE TAKEN
A $70,000 SALARY.

00:03:45,292 --> 00:03:47,060
IS THIS
YOUR FULL-TIME JOBS?
Rachel: FULL TIME.

00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,295
THIS IS ALL WE DO.
WE ACTUALLY MOVED.

00:03:48,295 --> 00:03:50,030
WE DRINK, SLEEP,
AND EAT THE JUMPAROO.

00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:51,364
WE MOVED FOR OUR BUSINESS.
IT'S ALL WE DO.

00:03:51,364 --> 00:03:53,066
O'Leary:
I THINK IT LOOKS DANGEROUS.

00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,268
I CAN TELL YOU THIS --
WE HAD A TRAMPOLINE GROWING UP.

00:03:55,268 --> 00:03:56,269
WE HAD A JUMPAROO,

00:03:56,269 --> 00:03:58,438
AND WE HAD KIDS
COMING OVER CONSTANTLY

00:03:58,438 --> 00:04:00,240
BECAUSE OF THESE TWO ITEMS.

00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:03,110
WE HAD PLENTY OF ACCIDENTS
ON THE TRAMPOLINE.

00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:06,113
EVERY YEAR,
105,000 KIDS GO TO THE E.R.

00:04:06,113 --> 00:04:07,147
DUE TO TRAMPOLINE INJURIES.
TRUE.

00:04:07,147 --> 00:04:08,982
AND WHAT'S THE RECORD
ON JUMPAROOS?

00:04:08,982 --> 00:04:10,484
NO ONE IN 30 YEARS
EVER GOT HURT ON IT.
IT'S -- IT'S A --

00:04:10,484 --> 00:04:12,219
WELL, THEN THAT JUST MEANS
YOU HAVEN'T SOLD ENOUGH.
HOW WOULD YOU KNOW?

00:04:12,219 --> 00:04:13,353
HOW MANY HAVE YOU SOLD?
[ LAUGHS ]

00:04:13,353 --> 00:04:16,323
OKAY. SO, WE'VE BEEN IN BUSINESS
FOR THE PAST 12 MONTHS,

00:04:16,323 --> 00:04:19,025
AND WE HAVE SOLD
1,200 UNITS.

00:04:19,025 --> 00:04:21,361
OKAY.
OUT OF THOSE 1,200 UNITS,
WE HAVE NOT HAD ONE CLAIM.

00:04:21,361 --> 00:04:22,996
WHAT WAS THE PRICE
YOU SOLD THEM AT?

00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:26,166
THE BIG ONE RETAILS FOR $399
ON OUR WEBSITE,

00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:28,268
AND THE SMALL ONE
RETAILS FOR $249.

00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,003
ARE YOU SELLING
IN RETAILERS?

00:04:30,003 --> 00:04:32,305
RIGHT NOW, WE TRAVEL AROUND
DIFFERENT SAM'S CLUB LOCATIONS.

00:04:32,305 --> 00:04:35,075
WE'RE THERE FOR A CERTAIN PERIOD
OF TIME, USUALLY 11 DAYS --

00:04:35,075 --> 00:04:36,343
YOU'RE DOING A ROAD SHOW.
Rachel: YES.

00:04:36,343 --> 00:04:38,078
WE'RE DOING THE ROAD SHOW
WITH SAM'S CLUB.

00:04:38,078 --> 00:04:40,280
SO, STEVE, 1,200 UNITS
YOU'VE SOLD IN 12 MONTHS.

00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,382
CORRECT.
HOW MANY OF THOSE
WERE THROUGH SAM'S CLUB,

00:04:42,382 --> 00:04:44,451
AND HOW MANY DID YOU SELL
OTHER WAYS?

00:04:44,451 --> 00:04:46,052
Steve: GREAT QUESTION.

00:04:46,052 --> 00:04:47,187
WE'VE SOLD 60 TOTAL
THROUGH SAM'S CLUB.

00:04:47,187 --> 00:04:48,221
WE WERE --
Herjavec: 60 UNITS?

00:04:48,221 --> 00:04:49,356
60. WE WERE IN THERE
FOR THREE WEEKS,

00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:50,991
AND WE SOLD OUT
OF PRODUCT.
OKAY.

00:04:50,991 --> 00:04:52,325
ONE QUESTION I HAVE
IS ALWAYS,

00:04:52,325 --> 00:04:55,028
WHEN YOU THINK ABOUT A PRODUCT
IN A RETAIL STORE,

00:04:55,028 --> 00:04:57,030
SIZE OF THE PRODUCT.

00:04:57,030 --> 00:05:00,167
IT'S ALWAYS A PROBLEM, BECAUSE
IF THEY COULD SELL 50 THINGS

00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:02,302
IN THAT ONE SPACE
INSTEAD OF ONE THING,

00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:04,070
THEY'RE GONNA GO
WITH THE 50.
Steve: YEAH.

00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:07,340
IS THIS K.D.-ABLE --
WHICH MEANS KNOCKED DOWN --

00:05:07,340 --> 00:05:09,109
SO THAT YOUR BOX IS SMALL?

00:05:09,109 --> 00:05:11,244
THE BOX IS 80 INCHES LONG,
20 INCHES WIDE,

00:05:11,244 --> 00:05:13,079
AND 5 INCHES THICK,
AND SO --

00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:15,115
SO THEY DON'T BREAK DOWN,
THOSE POLES?
THEY DON'T --

00:05:15,115 --> 00:05:17,150
THE POLES DO NOT BREAK DOWN
CURRENTLY.

00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,052
SO...
THAT -- THAT'S ACTUALLY
A PRETTY BIG CHALLENGE.

00:05:19,052 --> 00:05:20,153
IT IS.

00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:22,189
BECAUSE LET'S SAY
YOU WANT TO PUT IN 20 UNITS.

00:05:22,189 --> 00:05:24,157
YOU'RE GONNA REQUIRE
A FAIR AMOUNT OF SPACE HERE.

00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,993
WE -- WE HAVE -- WE --
NOW, SOME OF THOSE CAN STORE
IN BACK IN THE WAREHOUSE...

00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:29,262
THEY CAN.
...WHICH IS WHAT
THEY'RE PROBABLY DOING.

00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:32,165
BUT TO BE IN TOYS "R" US?
I'M MORE WORRIED ABOUT
THE DISPLAY ON THE FLOOR.

00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,302
Herjavec: I LOVE TOYS.

00:05:35,302 --> 00:05:39,039
MY WIFE SAYS I'M THE OLDEST
16-YEAR-OLD SHE KNOWS.

00:05:39,039 --> 00:05:42,075
IF I CAN PLAY WITH IT, MY KIDS
CAN PLAY WITH IT, I'LL BUY IT.

00:05:42,075 --> 00:05:44,978
GOT TO BE HONEST,
IT DOESN'T EXCITE ME.

00:05:44,978 --> 00:05:47,147
I'M NOT SAYING
IT'S A BAD PRODUCT.

00:05:47,147 --> 00:05:49,115
I JUST THINK MY KIDS
WOULD GET BORED WITH IT.

00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:52,319
'CAUSE WE HAVE A TRAMPOLINE.
WE'VE USED IT FOR 10 YEARS.

00:05:52,319 --> 00:05:54,120
Rachel: THIS IS NOT
A 15-MINUTE TOY.

00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,455
IF YOU PUT --
THIS IS A FOUR-HOUR TOY.

00:05:55,455 --> 00:05:57,123
PARENTS HAVE THE SAME EXPRESSION
YOU JUST DID

00:05:57,123 --> 00:05:58,258
WHERE THEY LOOK AT IT
AND THEY GO...

00:05:58,258 --> 00:05:59,392
"WHAT A DUMB IDEA."
..."I DON'T KNOW WHAT THIS IS."

00:05:59,392 --> 00:06:01,127
AND THEN THEY SEE THEIR KIDS
AND GO, "I GET IT."

00:06:01,127 --> 00:06:02,395
I DIDN'T WANT TO SAY,
"DUMB IDEA."

00:06:02,395 --> 00:06:04,164
WE'VE HEARD IT ALL.
AND GUESS WHAT.

00:06:04,164 --> 00:06:07,167
WE HAVE NOT HAD ONE PERSON
RETURN IT.

00:06:07,167 --> 00:06:09,002
John:
YOU SOUND LIKE YOU'RE DOING --

00:06:09,002 --> 00:06:12,038
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE CHUGGING ALONG.
YOU'RE FIGURING IT OUT, RIGHT?
MM-HMM.

00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,273
WHY DO YOU FEEL
YOU NEED PARTNERS?

00:06:13,273 --> 00:06:16,009
OKAY.
WE SUBMITTED TO 100 STORES.

00:06:16,009 --> 00:06:18,278
WE JUST MET WITH SAM'S CLUB.
WE SAT DOWN WITH THE BUYER.

00:06:18,278 --> 00:06:20,146
HE'S VERY EXCITED
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:21,147
BUT HE ASKED US...
YEAH.

00:06:21,147 --> 00:06:24,117
SO, WE WILL --
...TO PURCHASE 11,000 UNITS.

00:06:24,117 --> 00:06:25,151
THAT'S WHY WE NEED
THE SHARKS.

00:06:25,151 --> 00:06:27,020
FLAT-OUT.
BECAUSE WE ARE
TALKING ABOUT --

00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:30,023
IF WE DO WHAT WE DID IN THE
FIRST COUPLE LOCATIONS AT SAM'S,

00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:31,491
IF WE DO SOMETHING
SIMILAR TO THAT,

00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:34,060
THAT'S AROUND FOUR JUMPAROOS
A DAY IN 100 LOCATIONS.

00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,129
THAT IS A $1.3 MILLION
PURCHASE ORDER.

00:06:36,129 --> 00:06:39,232
SO, RIGHT NOW YOU NEED MONEY
SO YOU CAN MANUFACTURE MORE.

00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:43,303
WHEN I FIRST STARTED, I HAD
A LITTLE EARRING ORGANIZER,

00:06:43,303 --> 00:06:45,305
AND JCPenney SAID TO ME,

00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:49,309
"LORI, IF YOU CAN GET
THE CHICAGOLAND AREA TO BUY,

00:06:49,309 --> 00:06:51,077
THEN WE'LL TAKE YOU
NATIONWIDE."

00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:53,246
SO EVERY WEEKEND,
I WENT TO A DIFFERENT JCPenney

00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,381
AND I STOOD THERE ALL DAY

00:06:54,381 --> 00:06:56,383
DEMONSTRATING
THE SLIDING EARRING STANDS

00:06:56,383 --> 00:06:59,119
AND SHOWING MY PRODUCT
AND PULLING PEOPLE OVER.

00:06:59,119 --> 00:07:01,288
AND IT WAS A 12-HOUR DAY
EACH DAY.

00:07:01,288 --> 00:07:03,290
AND I SOLD ENOUGH
AND I GOT IN.

00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:05,091
SO THERE'S TWO OF YOU.

00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:07,327
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO GO IN,
DEMONSTRATE --

00:07:07,327 --> 00:07:09,262
BRING KIDS,
JUMP UP AND DOWN.

00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:11,164
HOW ARE YOU GONNA
GET 100 OF YOU?

00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:14,000
FOR ME RIGHT NOW, I'M OUT.

00:07:17,003 --> 00:07:18,204
THERE'S YOUR CHALLENGE,
RIGHT?

00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:20,307
SO, A-AS -- AS A SELF-CONTAINED,
FROM-HOME BUSINESS,

00:07:20,307 --> 00:07:21,374
THIS IS GREAT.

00:07:21,374 --> 00:07:24,044
NOW YOU WANT TO TAKE
THAT BIG STAIR STEP.

00:07:24,044 --> 00:07:26,112
BUT MONEY
ISN'T YOUR ONLY ISSUE,

00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:28,315
BECAUSE ONCE
YOU'RE IN 100 STORES,

00:07:28,315 --> 00:07:31,318
THE AGGRAVATION FACTOR
GOES THROUGH THE ROOF.

00:07:31,318 --> 00:07:35,388
AND YOU WILL GET TO THE POINT
WHERE SOMEBODY GETS HURT.

00:07:35,388 --> 00:07:37,424
IT'S JUST INEVITABLE.

00:07:37,424 --> 00:07:39,492
THERE'S IDIOTS EVERYWHERE,
AND YOU CAN'T PROTECT

00:07:39,492 --> 00:07:42,162
AGAINST SOMEONE SPRAINING
THEIR ANKLE, BREAKING AN ANKLE.

00:07:42,162 --> 00:07:44,464
IF I'D PARTNER WITH YOU,
EVERY TIME WE SOLD ONE,

00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:47,133
I'D HAVE TO CROSS MY FINGERS
AND CROSS MY TOES

00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,102
THAT IT WASN'T MY KIDS
THAT BROKE THEIR ANKLE.

00:07:49,102 --> 00:07:50,403
THAT'S JUST MY NATURE.

00:07:50,403 --> 00:07:53,340
AND SO I-I DON'T SEE MYSELF
BEING A GOOD PARTNER FOR YOU,

00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,274
SO I'M OUT.

00:07:56,076 --> 00:07:58,244
THIS IS A KID MAGNET.

00:07:58,244 --> 00:08:01,314
I DON'T THINK ANY ADULT
CAN UNDERSTAND HOW FUN IT IS

00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:03,416
UNTIL YOU SEE YOUR KIDS
JUMPING ON IT.

00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,285
AND IT IS SAFER THAN A TRAMPO--
Herjavec:
IT -- YEAH, LISTEN TO ME.

00:08:05,285 --> 00:08:07,454
I HAVE AN IMMENSE AMOUNT
OF RESPECT

00:08:07,454 --> 00:08:13,126
OF PEOPLE THAT TAKE AN IDEA
AND CREATE A COMPANY OUT OF IT.

00:08:13,126 --> 00:08:15,061
BUT I GOT TO REALLY
BELIEVE IN THE PRODUCT.

00:08:15,061 --> 00:08:17,464
I DON'T SEE THIS
TAKING OVER THE TRAMPOLINE

00:08:17,464 --> 00:08:20,100
OR BEING A SUPPLEMENT
TO THAT BUSINESS.

00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:23,269
SO IT JUST --
IT DOESN'T EXCITE ME THAT WAY.

00:08:23,269 --> 00:08:24,270
I'M OUT.

00:08:28,241 --> 00:08:30,043
WHAT EXCITES ME
IS MAKING MONEY.

00:08:30,043 --> 00:08:32,278
YOU KNOW, I DON'T CARE
IF THEY'RE BOUNCING UPSIDE DOWN

00:08:32,278 --> 00:08:34,314
OR WHATEVER OR HANGING
LIKE A PRISONER IN A CAGE

00:08:34,314 --> 00:08:36,182
AS LONG AS
YOU'RE MAKING MONEY.

00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:38,051
[ LAUGHS ]
THAT'S ALL I CARE ABOUT.

00:08:38,051 --> 00:08:41,154
BUT TO REALLY SCALE THIS PUPPY,
YOU'VE GOT SOME BIG CHALLENGES

00:08:41,154 --> 00:08:44,057
BECAUSE OF THE FLOOR SPACE,
THE FOOTPRINT OF THE PRODUCT.

